 Puppet 4 Services : Learn how to abstract from puppet code :
 Means : Without modification to the Puppet code or passing parameters to classes, hiera provides a lookup data-source. Enabling custom values to be retrieved from configuration data rather than within the code.
 --Download the ntp_start.tgz to your home directory --> Move into the /etc/puppetlabs/code environments/production/modules directory --> Expand the archive with sudo tar -xzvf ~ntp_start.tgz
 
 #run puppet apply
 sudo puppet apply -d -e 'include ntp'
 sudo puppet apply -d -e 'include ntp' | grep hiera
 
 
